        "skillName": "Assassin’s Strike",
        "stat": "dex",
        "definition": "<p>When ambushing a target, a Criminal can make an Assassin&rsquo;s Strike roll against the target&rsquo;s Awareness roll to conceal themselves after an attack. This ability can be used in any situation but imposes penalties based on light and cover conditions. Multiple opponents can each roll to spot the Criminal.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>In Melee range:</strong> -3 Mod.</li>\n<li><strong>In Light:</strong> -5 Mod.</li>\n<li><strong>In Darkness:</strong> +5 Mod.</li>\n<li><strong>In Dim Light:</strong> +2 Mod.</li>\n<li><strong>In a Heavily Crowded Area:</strong> +3 Mod.</li>\n<li><strong>In a Silent Area:</strong> -1 Mod.</li>\n<li><strong>Beyond 20m of the Target:</strong> +3 Mod.</li>\n</ul>",
